[normal]that 
[normal]we look across the range in its entirety. That is the first thing. In order to believe that the lower end of the range is what we should focus on, that we should rule out the rest of that range, you would have to believe that the positive feedbacks that come from water vapour, for example, and through the melting of ice and reduced reflection of the sun back out of the atmosphere, were offset with very strong negative feedbacks due to cloud. That is not evidenced at all at the moment. So that is one thing that we look at.
[normal]              
